    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="245">
      <subfield code="a">Fast phase manipulation of the single nuclear spin in solids by rotating fields</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="260">
      <subfield code="c">2017-03-13</subfield>
      <subfield code="t">published</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="300">
      <subfield code="a">8</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="520">
      <subfield code="a">We propose fast phase gates of single nuclear spins interacting with single electron spins. The gate operation utilizes geometric phase shifts of the electron spin induced by fast and slow rotating fields; the path difference depending on nuclear-spin states enables nuclear phase shifts. The gate time is inversely proportional to the frequency of the slow rotating field. As an example, we use nitrogen-vacancy centers in diamond, and show, in principle, the phase-gate time orders of magnitude to be shorter than previously reported. We also confirmed the robustness of the gate against decoherence and systematic errors.</subfield>
      <subfield code="9">APS</subfield>
    </datafield>
